				<div class="info">
					<span class="printuser avatarhover"><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/sharpembrace" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(6032914); return false;"  ><img class="small" src="http://www.wikidot.com/avatar.php?userid=6032914&amp;amp;size=small&amp;amp;timestamp=1610203366" alt="SharpEmbrace" style="background-image:url(http://www.wikidot.com/userkarma.php?u=6032914)"/></a><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/sharpembrace" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(6032914); return false;" >SharpEmbrace</a></span> <span class="odate time_1581617818 format_%25e%20%25b%20%25Y%2C%20%25H%3A%25M%7Cagohover">13 Feb 2020 18:16</span>
														</div>
			</div>
			<div class="content" id="post-content-4499756">
									

<p>I liked this and upvoted, but I think the dialogue is a little clunky in some places.</p>
<div class="collapsible-block">
<div class="collapsible-block-folded"><a class="collapsible-block-link" href="javascript:;">donk</a></div>
<div class="collapsible-block-unfolded" style="display:none">
<div class="collapsible-block-unfolded-link"><a class="collapsible-block-link" href="javascript:;">donk</a></div>
<div class="collapsible-block-content">
<blockquote>
<p>Dammit, I am stuck!</p>
</blockquote>
<p>I can't imagine someone saying something so nonchalant in a life or death scenario. I get that Clockworks can be wooden in their speech and that this is set in the late 19th century, but it still comes off as odd. I would put &quot;Help me, brother!&quot; instead, as this conveys his vulnerability and the intensity of the situation better.</p>
<blockquote>
<p>Wait here, Dr. Heart, I will inquire.</p>
</blockquote>
<p>I feel like inquire is also a little emotionless, given that it is preceded by him reaching for his pistol. I think you were trying to convey that Mr. Schroeder is unafraid and calm, but this suggests indifference rather than dominance. I would say &quot;Don't worry about it, Dr. Heart. I will settle this.&quot; This shows professionalism and a calm demeanour without compromising confidence.</p>
<blockquote>
<p>You should have been useful first.</p>
</blockquote>
<p>I think that the Clockworks wouldn't have bothered killing the civilian unless they were genuinely annoyed by his lack of compliance. Especially having considered that they already had their information and wanted to waste no time in reaching Dr. Heart. Thus, it would make more sense to have dialogue that displays this frustration. I would use something along the lines of &quot;Is telling us that too difficult for you, you pathetic imbecile?&quot; This conveys disdain for others, a good way to antagonise your antagonists, and reinforces the urgency of their mission, whilst justifying their execution more rationally.</p>
<blockquote>
<p>Give me what is stolen. Give me now!</p>
</blockquote>
<p>This doesn't show the reverence with which they hold objects like the elixir and makes the Colussus seem unintelligent. I'm sure the latter was intentional but could be done further. I would use &quot;Return the relic, thief! You suffer now. A lot.&quot; This sets up for him to be outsmarted by Donkman better and shows his aggression towards Heart.</p>
<p>These aren't super glaring issues but I thought you might want to consider them.</p>
</div>
</div>
</div>

							</div>

